EU Plan Would Back Private-Sector Infrastructure Bonds, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-02-28T02:33:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/eu-plan-would-back-private-sector-infrastructure-bonds-ft-says.html
European Union Economic and Monetary
Commissioner Olli Rehn and European Investment Bank Chairman
Philippe Maystadt will today reveal a plan to use European Union
funds to guarantee private-sector bonds for big infrastructure
projects, the Financial Times reported, citing a draft document
detailing the plan, which is intended to boost funding for
projects hit by spending cuts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 